metadata.title: Beechcraft Super King Air
aws::graph::propositions: All nine occupants aboard were killed in an unspecified Beechcraft Super King Air accident.
Two people on the ground were injured in an unspecified Beechcraft Super King Air accident.
A King Air 350i Nigerian Air Force aircraft crashed near Kaduna International Airport on May 21, 2021.
The King Air 350i crash on May 21, 2021 killed all 11 people on board.
Chief of Army Staff Ibrahim Attahiru was among those killed in the King Air 350i crash on May 21, 2021.
A B350 King Air carrying a United States Marine and three contractors crashed into a ricefield at Ampatuan, Philippines on February 6, 2025.
All four occupants aboard the B350 King Air were killed upon impact in the February 6, 2025 crash.
A B200 King Air with registration PH-ZAZ crashed on takeoff at London Southend Airport on July 13, 2025.
The B200 King Air was operating as Zeusch Aviation Flight 1 when it crashed.
London Southend Airport is located in Southend-on-Sea, England.
The B200 King Air crash on July 13, 2025 resulted in 4 fatalities.
A B300 King Air with registration N534AW crashed on approach at Chinle Municipal Airport on August 5, 2025.
The B300 King Air was owned by CSI Aviation.
The B300 King Air was operating as CSI534/SANDIA534 medical transport when it crashed.
The B300 King Air crash on August 5, 2025 resulted in the deaths of both pilots, the flight paramedic, and flight nurse.

text:
All nine occupants aboard were killed; two people on the ground were injured.
May 21, 2021: A King Air 350i Nigerian Air Force crashed near Kaduna International Airport, killing all 11 on board, including Chief of Army Staff Ibrahim Attahiru.
February 6, 2025: A B350 King Air carrying a United States Marine and three contractors crashed into a ricefield at Ampatuan, Philippines. All four occupants aboard were killed upon impact.
July 13, 2025: A B200 (PH-ZAZ) operating as Zeusch Aviation Flight 1 crashed on takeoff at London Southend Airport, Southend-on-Sea, England, resulting in 4 fatalities.
August 5, 2025: A B300 (N534AW) owned by CSI Aviation operating as CSI534/ SANDIA534 medical transport, crashed on approach at Chinle Municipal Airport, resulting in the deaths of both pilots, the flight paramedic and flight nurse.
